Problem 2: Traversal Application

Tree:

        root
       /    \
     home    var
    /   \      \
  user  docs    log
  /
config
a) Alphabetical listing (BST)

Use Inorder traversal
Reason: gives sorted order in BST

b) Total directory size

Use Postorder traversal
Reason: process children before parent

c) Backup directory structure

Use Preorder traversal
Reason: copy root first, then subdirectories

d) Traversals
Inorder (LNR)
config → user → home → docs → root → var → log
Preorder (NLR)
root → home → user → config → docs → var → log
Postorder (LRN)
config → user → docs → home → log → var → root
e) Why postorder for deletion
Deletes children before parent
Prevents dangling references
Safe memory cleanup
